  "prompt": "Operator: abs (out = |x|). Input shapes: [1, 128], [4, 2048], [32, 4096]; perf shape [32, 4096]. Output shape: same_as_input. Dtype: float16. Layout: contiguous. Axis: null. Tiling: flatten each test shape to 1D (size = product of dims) inside the host launcher; the kernel takes `size: int` and tiles 1D with `asc2.tensor(x_ptr, [size])`, `asc2.load(x_gm, [tile_size], offsets=[tile_offset])`, `asc2.store(out, out_gm, offsets=[tile_offset])` \u2014 all ranks 1. PERF: use a WIDE tile TILE_SIZE=2048 (NOT the 128 correctness default) to keep the AIV vector pipeline busy and amortise per-tile MTE setup, mirroring the ops-math arch35 elementwise tile policy (math/abs/op_host/arch35/abs_tiling_arch35.cpp); on camodel this raises the ratio vs hand-written aclnnAbs from ~0.20 (TILE=128) to ~0.93 (TILE=2048) at [32, 4096]. CORE_NUM=16; size must be a multiple of TILE_SIZE*CORE_NUM=32768 (aligned_only); partition tile_per_core via `asc2.range(tile_per_block, unroll_factor=2, parallel=True)`. Tail: aligned_only. Accumulator: null. Tolerance: atol=1e-3, rtol=1e-3 against np.abs(x). Platform: Ascend950PR_9599. Build/run: python3.11 kernel.py -r Model -v Ascend950PR_9599. Evidence: kernel.py (skills-on adds design.md + verification.md).",
